The paper focuses on training methods for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in various fields of computer science such as natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the difficulties of training these networks, which is a topic often studied in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image recognition tasks, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
